                    <comment id="12589550" author="mreutegg" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2008 14:29:40 +0100"  >After some reconsideration I decided to only implement the first option. I think an inconsistency should always trigger some manual intervention and with the newly added consistency fix (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1428&quot; title=&quot;Add API for selective bundle consistency check (Jackrabbit-specific)&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-1428&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) this is now possible.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Which means for now this is basically about turning &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1326&quot; title=&quot;Log path of missing node when re-indexing fails&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-1326&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in a more manageable form.&lt;br/&gt;
